                          </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a05">
                          <desc>
                          The manuscript contains the following marginalia:
                            <locus target="#95v"/> top margin: Note about canticle two, the Prayer of Moses
                            <locus target="#95v"/>, top margin: Note about canticle two, the Prayer of Moses.
                            <locus target="#99r"/>, top margin: Note about canticle six, the Prayer of Manasseh.
                            <locus target="#103r"/>, top margin: Note about canticle twelve, the Prayer of Isaiah.
                            <locus from="105v" to="106v"/>, top margin: Note on the meaning of the Song of Songs.
                            <locus from="112r" to="113v"/>: marginal notation.
                            <locus target="#ir"/>, <locus from="132v" to="133v"/>: Scrawls.
                            </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e01">
                          <desc>
                        Scribal intervention:
                        words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#9r #65v #77r #92v #106r"/> etc.);
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#105v"/>);
                        and in the upper margin with a symbol (I) marking the location where the text is to be inserted<locus target="#20v"/>, line 2);
                        erasure markings are visible <locus target="#106r #121"/>").
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                        Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate
                        script size. But #where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters.
                      </desc>
                    </item>

